description:
No you’re not seeing things, that is a Sopwith Camel scout attacking a Ju 87 Stuka. But surely, you say, they’re planes from two different wars, their designs nearly 25 years apart? Surely they would never have met in combat?

Well, yes and no.

How this unlikely pair came face to face takes a bit of explaining. It’s the story of a warrior’s… Return to the Sky.
name: Return To The Sky

description:
The Sign of the Scorpion was their badge, and soon the Germans learned why…for the men of the Long Range Desert Group would fight as long as they drew breath.

Their raids were as fast as the sting of the scorpion, and twice as deadly!
name: Scourge Of The Desert

description:
On the retreat to Dunkirk, Sergeant-Major Mike Fletcher had hooked up with a trio of individuals separated from their units. Eventually they were captured and became POWs.

However, Mike saw some potential in this down-trodden and uninspired bunch. The Sergeant-Major was determined to turn them into proper soldiers once and for all!

First, all they had to do was escape…
name: "On The Run!"

description:
When Johnny Peace was called up to the army he refused to fight, refused to kill anyone…and he was branded a coward. So he went to war as a medical orderly. Not for him guns or grenades – his only weapons were his medical satchel and his courage.

A coward? Not Johnny Peace. There was probably never a braver man in the British Army!
name: No-Gun Hero

description: The Titans Companion is a comprehensive look back at the best-selling DC series! The history of the definite teen team is covered in Volume 1 through a series of interviews with fan-favorite creators Marv Wolfman, George Pérez, José Luis García-López, and Len Wein. Also included is a comprehensive Silver Age section featuring interviews with Neal Adams, Nick Cardy, and Dick Giordano, and Chris Claremont and Walter Simonson reflect on the X-Men/New Teen Titans crossover.
name: Volume One

description: Following in the footsteps of its predecessor, The Titans Companion 2 picks up where Volume 1 left off, covering the return of the Teen Titans to the top of the sales charts! Featuring interviews with Geoff Johns, Mike McKone, Peter David, Phil Jimenez, and others, it also contains an in-depth section on the top-rated Cartoon Network series! Read what the producers and staff of the show have to say about adapting the Titans to the small screen! Plus Chuck Dixon, Mark Waid, Karl Kesel, and John Byrne on writing the current generation of Titans! More with Marv Wolfman and George Perez! Neal Adams on redesigning Robin! Artwork by Adams, Byrne, Jimenez, McKone, Perez and more! With an all-new cover by Mike McKone, The Titans Companion Volume 2 completes any Titans fan's collection!
name: Volume Two
Australia's new era in comics starts here

name: Winners Never Quit

description: Celebrating the epic romance of Bruce and Betty this collection follows the star-crossed lovers from their very first meeting to their historic wedding and beyond! With an all-new intro by Peter David.

The Travellers

Three teens have discovered colourful beings in the neighboorhood. It turns out that they are made of candy! And they are zombies! They call themselves the Travellers, as they are on a journey, and uncertain why they are back from the dead.

In Issue 2, we learn more about the teens and the Travellers, as both worlds start to collide!

The second issue of Brittle Hill delves deeper into the mysterious coloured beings who live in Brittle Hill. "The travellers" are venturing further into the town of Brittle Hill, and there are signs that indicate that is a good thing, AND a bad thing!
name: The Travellers

description: Metropolis is under mystical siege, and Emil is trapped inside S.T.A.R. Labs with an unlikely source of help. Lex Luthor has trapped Ted Kord and Michael Holt inside their Antarctic base, cutting them off from Booster Gold’s help. Superman and Lois Lane are trapped on an alternate Earth – and that’s not the worst of their troubles! Where can they turn for help?
name: Chaos, Part 2

description: This issue begins with the aftermath of the shootout from issue six at Schwarzenegger General Hospital, which resulted Deputy Correspondent Strunk confronted the mysterious foreign twin brothers, Johann and Frederic, as they kidnapped Melanie. We discover Strunk survived the gunfire exchange, but one of the brothers (Frederic) does not. Strunk has a new lead but soon learns Citizen National News is assuming the investigation. Meanwhile, P.I. and Raveena work to find out a way to save Melanie, and at the same time continue to uncover more of DeGuerre’s plot to re-establish the internet.

Having barely survived his first encounter with the Strongman, Barry heads to S.T.A.R. Labs for medical treatment and the CCPD investigates the scene of the crime. Is there more to last issue's bank robbery than meets the eye?
name: Freak Show, Part 2: Who Let the Chimps Out?

description: The crisis shifts to Nil, homeworld of the Monitor. And new versions of Dr. Fate, Green Arrow and Power Girl like none you've ever seen burst into action.
name: Chapter Nineteen

volume.name: Infinite Crisis: Fight For the Multiverse

description: Four tales of suspense starring superhumanity's detective agency of choice! Madrox investigates a suicide case that isn't what it initially seems! Banshee is suspected of murder and sets out to clear her name, but ends up clashing with…an actual banshee! Strong Guy asks M out on a date. (Yikes!) And Layla Miller races the clock! It's X-FACTOR action as only veteran scribe Peter David can provide! Collecting X-FACTOR (1986) #237-240.
name: Volume 17

description:
Bart Simpson may be best known as an underachiever at school, but there is no title that this juvenile jokester holds more dearly that that of class clown. Springfield Elementary School is his domain and it is there that the prince of pranks rules supreme in the classroom, on the playground, and in after-school detention. Join the fun as Bart resurrects the car crunching, fire breathing behemoth known as Truckasaurus; foils the evil plans of Dr. Colossus; deciphers an ancient riddle; pals around with a new kid from way out of town; and gets expelled from school. Watch Bart go to the head of the class and take his place at top of the dishonor roll!!!

Contains Bart Simpson Comics #33-37

*Elementary School Dropout: After pulling another prank on Principal Skinner, Bart is expelled from school. What would first seem like a dream come true, Bart struggles with life with no school.

*A Load of Trouble: Lisa ruins her dress and tries to do her laundry by herself with disastrous results

*Mr. Bart Krabappel: After his prank makes Ms. Krabappel without a home, she moves into the Simpsons' home and makes Bart's life miserable.

*Willie and The Weasels: Learn the secret of Groundskeeper Willie's past as a rock icon.

*Signs of Intelligent Life: Bart befriends a boy from "way out of town" and they wreak havoc on Springfield.

*Barty and Milhousy: Bart and Milhouse decide to play a game of "Itchy and Scratchy"

*The Return of the Truckasaurus: While at the garbage dump Bart and Otto discover Truckasaurus.

*Bart vs Bart: Bart fights with his inner demon

*One For All and Alpha One: Bart and Milhouse discover an ancient book.

*Going Postal: Bart and MIlhouse try to mail a letter

*Today's Science Prank with Professor Frink: Prof. Frink shows readers how to do a prank involving an egg and a wine bottle

*One Flew Over the Retirement Castle: Bart has to do a report on the great depression and what better way to see the depressed then to visit his grandfather,

*Burger Meister

*Ten-iator: Dr. Colossus has turned everyone in Springfield into 10 yr olds. Now its up to Bartman and his rag tag group of child heroes to stop him
name: Bart Simpson Comics

deck: The Valley of Death Alliance aka VODA is set in the Outpouring Universe and follows the villainous group through their recruiting, planning, and execution of super villain schemes.
description: Set in the Outpouring Universe where powers have just come to Earth from a supernatural being. Deadeye was at one time a modern day Robin Hood biker leader until one day the Outpouring happened and his entire gang was killed as a result. Deadeye has now sworn revenge for this act. He now travels into the desert to meet up with The Butcher to gather information on the Legendary Mole with the intent of recruiting this 'Mole' to a new villainous group he is forming. This new face of fear Deadeye calls VODA.

deck: The Valley of Death Alliance aka VODA is set in the Outpouring Universe and follows the villainous group through their recruiting, planning, and execution of super villain schemes.
description: Deadeye and Mr. Mole search for information concerning the 'Ghost Killer' and run into the Heroes United in the process. Enter Invincible, The Link, and Samuel Payne. How will our villians deal with this new foe.

Deadeye and Mr. Mole set out to capture and recruit the Ghost Killer known as Gorilla Ghost. Along the way they run into a mysterious new group made up of Senator Luther Jennings, Sheriff Big Billy Bob, and the mystical Maloney.

The Valley of Death Alliance aka VODA is set in the Outpouring Universe and follows the villainous group through their recruiting, planning, and execution of super villain schemes. VODA 3 finishes up the introductory arc and initial recruiting phase by Deadeye for VODA.
